   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>OUTLINE EIGHT PROPHESYING</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>IN THE CHURCH MEETINGS</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>FOR THE ORGANIC BUILDING UP</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>OF THE CHURCH AS THE BODY OF CHRIST Scripture Reading: 1 Cor 14:31, 24-25, 14-16, 32, 23a, 26, 19, 1, 39, 12, 33; 1 Pet 4:11; John 21:15; 2 Cor 5:14-15; 4:16; 1 John 1:7, 9; Rev 2:7; 1 Thes 5:17; 1 John 1:2-3, 6; Gal 5:16; Phil 1:19-21; Eph 5:18; Acts 4:31; 1 Tim 2:4; Col 3:16; Phil 3:8-10; Col 1:28-29; 1 Cor 14:26 Prophesying is divine speaking, God s oracle: One who prophesies or one who is a prophet 1 Cor 14:31, 29-30, 37 is one who receives revelations of the mysteries concerning Christ and the church Eph 3:5 and then speaks for God, speaks forth God, and even speaks God, dispenses God, into others, having God s oracle 1 Pet 4:11 .</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>In both the Old Testament and the New Testament prophesying denotes the divine speaking, the divine oracle.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Prophesying is not ordinary words spoken in a natural way but rather a speaking in the element of God s divinity: To prophesy we must speak with the divine element.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Without the divine element, our speaking is not prophesying; instead it is only empty talk without God s speaking, without reality, and without any divine revelation or ministry of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The more of the divine element there is in our speaking, the more our speaking is prophesying.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To have God s oracle we must possess the element, essence, and substance of the Triune God: We must be filled with the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>We must be soaked with the Word.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>We must experience the divine life.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>We must pray ourselves into the Spirit all the time.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>We must walk in the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>All can have the oracle of God 1 Cor 14:31; 1 Pet 4:11: Prophesying is speaking with God s oracle, God s divine speaking.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Each one must be in the Spirit, having an exercised and released spirit 1 Cor 14:14-16, 32 where God s oracle is to afford a way for God to speak.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Each one must have a clear, sober, mind 1 Cor 14:15, 19 to understand and remember the things revealed to us by God to render the human cooperation to the divine oracle.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>When all prophesy, having God s oracle, a new one in the meeting is convicted by all and judged by all, the secrets of his heart become manifest, and he worships God, reporting that God is really among the saints 1 Cor 14:24-25.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>We must speak in a divine way with the divine element by the divine life.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>In our prophesying, the divine speaking, we minister Christ into others; we dispense the very Christ we have received, experienced, and enjoyed to others.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>To prophesy in the meetings of the church, we must care for our whole being spirit, soul, and body: A presented body to come together 1 Cor 14:23a, 26.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>A sober, clear mind to pray, sing, and speak 1 Cor 14:15, 19.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>An emotion that desires earnestly to prophesy 1 Cor 14:1, 39 and that is zealous to prophesy 1 Cor 14:12 .</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>A will that chooses to prophesy in a timely way when to begin and when to cease 1 Cor 14:32-33.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>An exercised spirit to pray, sing, bless, and prophesy 1 Cor 14:14-16, 31-32.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>To prophesy in the meetings of the church, we must live a proper, normal Christian life: Loving the Lord John 21:15, 17; Rev 2:4; Eph 6:24.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Devoting ourselves to the Lord in His love 2 Cor 5:14-15.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Being revived every morning by enjoying the Lord in the Word to have a new start each day 2 Cor 4:16; Lam 3:22-23; Prov 4:18; Jer 15:16; Psa 119:147-148.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Being enlightened and thoroughly dealing with our sins by confessing 1 John 1:7, 9.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Living a victorious, overcoming life daily Rev 2:7; Rom 10:12b.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Praying unceasingly by calling on the Lord continually 1 Thes 5:17; 2 Tim 2:22.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Abiding in fellowship with the Lord to partake of the divine life and to walk in the divine light 1 Cor 1:9; 1 John 1:2-3, 6-7.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Walking by and according to our spirit mingled with the Spirit Gal 5:16; Rom 8:4.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Living Christ for His magnification by the bountiful supply of the Spirit of Jesus Christ Phil 1:19-21; Gal 2:20.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Being filled with the Spirit inwardly and outwardly Acts 13:52; Eph 5:18; Acts 4:31, 8; 13:9.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Learning and gaining a full knowledge of the truth and letting the word of Christ dwell in us richly, thus keeping a rich storage of the Lord s word 1 Tim 2:4; Col 3:16; John 15:7; 1 John 2:14.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Accumulating the experiences of Christ Phil 3:8-10, 12-14.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Speaking Christ to all kinds of people at all times Col 1:28-29; 2 Tim 4:2.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Functioning in all kinds of meetings in mutuality: By praying 1 Cor 14:14-15; Acts 2:42; 12:5, 12, 17.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>By speaking and singing the hymns Eph 5:19; Col 3:16; 1 Cor 14:15, 26.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>By teaching 1 Cor 14:26, 6; Acts 5:42.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>By revelation 1 Cor 14:26, 6.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>By prophesying 1 Cor 14:5, 24, 31, 6.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>By knowledge 1 Cor 14:6.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>By exhorting Heb 10:25.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>By testifying Acts 15:12.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>By preaching the gospel Acts 5:42.</S>
